# Network Traffic Monitoring Program

This project is a C++ program designed to monitor and analyze network traffic. The program listens to network packets, collects data, and performs various analyses on the data.

## Requirements

- C++ Compiler (GCC or Clang recommended)
- pcap Library (for network packet capturing)

## How to Use

1. Clone this repository to your local machine.
2. Compile the C++ program using your preferred compiler.
3. Run the executable.
4. The program will start capturing network packets and display real-time statistics on the console.

## Features

- Collects and analyzes TCP and UDP packets separately.
- Calculates the total number of packets and average packet sizes for each protocol.
- Tracks total data transfer (in bytes) for each protocol.
- Provides timestamp information for peak data usage periods.
- Allows users to filter data by protocol, IP address, or port number.

## Contributions

Contributions to this project are welcome. If you have any suggestions, bug reports, or improvements, feel free to create a pull request.

